originalText.text: I cannot tell Dr. Moliver is unprofessional. Maybe he is a good doctor. But the office staff is really horrible. They NEVER call you back. Every time you are at the office it's a favor if they even respond to you. The efficiency of the office is 3%. The excellent phlebotomist works for him. She is really good. But the time management at this office DOES NOT EXIST. There is always a line. I needed to have vaccination in order to go to India. I had to find out on the internet what I have to have. My husband, my son and me had to come 6 times to the doctor (paying co-pay of course, CASH ONLY, NO CARDS) plus 3 times for vaccination and an extra time for tablets. 10 times!!!! NEVER MORE will they see us at this office.
